choices.text: the solution to problems in the family. Deliberating about the connections between the phenomenon of moving to another country, family conditions and the ability to preserve relationships or to create a new family for oneself, it becomes clear that to a considerable extent that, the problems found by the content analysis (low-level guarantees for spouses, reduced effectiveness of matrimonial bankruptcy legislation for situations when the need arises while staying in Estonia, the permanent nature of separation of the family into two temporally separated camps, that do not include cultural values while making life decisions and forming a family) are objectively presented in the confessional doctrines of the studied churches, and the doctrines of other Estonian churches and sects, whose data was later analyzed by the survey: teachings on the family, the ability to survive in life on one's own, the secure stable peace of soul; and teachings on the conservation of partners. It should be noted that those teachings that constitute universal preparation and experiential skill, for example, the forgiveness of our own sins, the ability to ask for forgiveness, the expiation of pathological history of non-learning, or a stable peace of the soul based on communication with God and man, are found in most confessional doctrines in equal measure. Other features differ in their level of commitment, techniques of calculation, symmetry and semantics, which are caused mainly by the condemnation culture of sexuality and in “hindered” by the history of slavery of life conditions.
